node.text:
FOLLOW @ecomdave for more Amazon tips

Imagine buying 500 units of a product.

Each unit cost $3, Which means you spent $1,500

You spend $500 to ship the product from China to Amazon warehouses.

Total investment of $2,000

You sell that product for $20 per unit.

Amazon then packages and ships your product to its customers all over the world.

500 units at a $20 a pop means $10,000 in total revenue

After Amazon takes its 25% in fees

We are left with $7,500 in revenue

After our initial product cost of $2,000

We are left with $5,500 profit from one product.

Learn the Exact Step-by-Step Process
